parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission and drivetrain components can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, and may result in costly repairs.
symptoms: The vehicle experiences difficulty shifting gears
grinding or screeching noises when shifting

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The mixing of engine oil and coolant can cause engine damage, leading to a loss of power, overheating, and potentially catastrophic engine failure, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.
The failure of the catalytic converter can cause the vehicle to fail emissions tests, lead to decreased fuel efficiency, and potentially cause engine damage, which can result in costly repairs.
A defective muffler can cause excessive noise, decreased fuel efficiency, and potentially lead to engine damage, which can result in costly repairs.
A defective flywheel can cause clutch failure, leading to difficulty shifting gears, which can result in accidents or leave the driver stranded.

The failure of the alternator can cause the battery to drain, leading to a loss of electrical power, which can result in the vehicle stalling or failing to start, potentially causing accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The battery warning light is illuminated on the dashboard
the vehicle's electrical systems (such as the radio or lights) malfunction or fail
the vehicle stalls or fails to start
the alternator belt is worn or broken.
